					<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl tracking-tight font-normal text-gray-100 uppercase">frequently asked questions</h2>
					
				</div>
				<div id="accordion-flush" data-accordion="collapse" data-active-classes="bg-white  text-gray-900" data-inactive-classes="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
					<!-- Accordion-1 -->
				  <h2 id="accordion-flush-heading-1">
					  <button type="button" class="flex items-center justify-between w-full py-5 font-medium rtl:text-right text-gray-500 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 gap-3" data-accordion-target="#accordion-flush-body-1" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="accordion-flush-body-1">
						<span class="text-gray-400 ">What is Employer of Record (EOR) Services?</span>
						<svg data-accordion-icon class="w-3 h-3 rotate-180 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 10 6">
						  <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"/>
						</svg>
					  </button>
					</h2>
					<div id="accordion-flush-body-1" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-flush-heading-1">
					  <div class="py-5 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
						<p class="mb-2 text-gray-500">Employer of Record (EOR) services is a business arrangement where a third party takes on the responsibility of being the official employer for a group of workers. This includes handling payroll, taxes, and compliance with employment laws, while the workers perform their duties for another company.</p>
						
					  </div>
					</div>
					<!-- Accordion-2 -->
					<h2 id="accordion-flush-heading-2">
					  <button type="button" class="flex items-center justify-between w-full py-5 font-medium rtl:text-right text-gray-500 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 gap-3" data-accordion-target="#accordion-flush-body-2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-flush-body-2">
						<span class="text-gray-400 ">Why would a company use EOR services?</span>
						<svg data-accordion-icon class="w-3 h-3 rotate-180 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 10 6">
						  <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"/>
						</svg>
					  </button>
					</h2>
					<div id="accordion-flush-body-2" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-flush-heading-2">
					  <div class="py-5 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
						<p class="mb-2 text-gray-500">A company may use Employer of Record (EOR) services to simplify global expansion, ensure compliance with local labor laws, reduce administrative burdens, and focus on core business functions.</p>
						
					  </div>
					</div>
					<!-- Accordion-3 -->
					<h2 id="accordion-flush-heading-3">
					  <button type="button" class="flex items-center justify-between w-full py-5 font-medium rtl:text-right text-gray-500 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 gap-3" data-accordion-target="#accordion-flush-body-3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-flush-body-3">
						<span class="text-gray-400 ">How does EOR differ from traditional staffing or outsourcing?</span>
						<svg data-accordion-icon class="w-3 h-3 rotate-180 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 10 6">
						  <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"/>
						</svg>
					  </button>
					</h2>
					<div id="accordion-flush-body-3" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-flush-heading-3">
					  <div class="py-5 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
						<p class="mb-2 text-gray-500">Employer of Record (EOR) services make a third party the official employer, handling payroll and compliance while the client maintains control over tasks. Traditional staffing or outsourcing involves the third party managing both employment and tasks, often for longer durations and broader scopes.</p>
						
					  </div>
					</div>
				  </div>
				  <!-- Accordion-4 -->
				  <h2 id="accordion-flush-heading-4">
					<button type="button" class="flex items-center justify-between w-full py-5 font-medium rtl:text-right text-gray-500 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 gap-3" data-accordion-target="#accordion-flush-body-4" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-flush-body-4">
					  <span class="text-gray-400 ">What are the key benefits of using EOR services?</span>
					  <svg data-accordion-icon class="w-3 h-3 rotate-180 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 10 6">
						<path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"/>
					  </svg>
					</button>
				  </h2>
				  <div id="accordion-flush-body-4" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-flush-heading-4">
					<div class="py-5 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
					  <p class="mb-2 text-gray-500">Key benefits of using Employer of Record (EOR) services include simplified global expansion, ensured compliance with local labor laws, reduced administrative burden, enhanced focus on core business functions, cost-effectiveness, and flexibility in workforce management.</p>
					 
					</div>
				  </div>
			
				  <!-- Accordion-5 -->
				<h2 id="accordion-flush-heading-5">
				  <button type="button" class="flex items-center justify-between w-full py-5 font-medium rtl:text-right text-gray-500 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 gap-3" data-accordion-target="#accordion-flush-body-5" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-flush-body-5">
					<span class="text-gray-400 ">What types of businesses benefit most from EOR services?</span>
					<svg data-accordion-icon class="w-3 h-3 rotate-180 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 10 6">
					  <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"/>
					</svg>
				  </button>
				</h2>
				<div id="accordion-flush-body-5" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-flush-heading-5">
				  <div class="py-5 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
					<p class="mb-2 text-gray-500">
						
						Businesses that benefit most from Employer of Record (EOR) services are those involved in global expansion, startups entering new markets, companies with short-term or project-based staffing needs, and organizations seeking to streamline international workforce management without setting up legal entities in each location.</p>
					
				  </div>
				</div>
			  </div>
				</div>
				
				
				  
			
			</section>
